{"title_page": "Diamond and Silk", "text_new": "{{short description|American video bloggers}}\n \n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Diamond and Silk\n| image              = File:Diamond and Silk on Info Wars April 2018.jpg\n| image_size         = 240px\n| caption            = Diamond and Silk (left to right) on ''[[InfoWars]]'' in 2018\n| birth_name         = Lynnette Hardaway (\"Diamond\")<br /> Rochelle Richardson (\"Silk\")\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]]\n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| education          = \n| occupation         = Social media personalities, political activists\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = The Viewers View\n| home_town          = [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]], U.S. \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- {{height|cm=X}} OR {{height|ft=X|in=Y}}-->\n| weight             = <!-- {{convert|X|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} or {{convert|X|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}} -->\n| television         = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| ethnicity          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] (2015\u2013present) <br /> [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] (until 2015)\n}}\n\t\n'''Lynnette Hardaway''' and '''Rochelle Richardson''', known as '''Diamond and Silk''', are American live-stream video bloggers, social media personalities, political activists and [[Fox Nation]] hosts whose tweets saying Covid19 death numbers have been inflated to hurt the administration, have resulted in them being temporarily banned from Twitter after they posted a tweet saying we all need to go out to get immunity, contradicting [[CDC]] advice.[https://www.salon.com/2020/04/08/diamond-and-silk-were-locked-out-of-twitter-for-suggesting-that-people-develop-immunity-to-coronavirus/]  They are known for their commentary in support of United States President [[Donald Trump]], and having utter contempt for scientific data and expert advice<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.redstate.com/jeffc/2020/03/31/diamond-and-silk-spin-preposterous-conspiracy-theory-about-coronavirus-deaths/|title=Diamond and Silk Spin Preposterous Conspiracy Theory About Coronavirus Deaths|last=Charles|first=Jeff|date=March 31 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 8 2020}}</ref>.\n\nThe two women received media attention during the 2016 campaign and again in April 2018 when they alleged that [[Facebook]] had notified them they were \"unsafe to the community.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://judiciary.house.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Diamond-and-Silk-Testimony.pdf|title=Diamond and Silk Testimony to House Judiciary Committee|website=Judiciary Committee, US House of Representatives|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121210526/https://judiciary.house.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Diamond-and-Silk-Testimony.pdf|archive-date=November 21, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>  In response, they accused Facebook of blocking and censoring their Facebook page.  There is, however, no evidence that Facebook blocked or censored Diamond and Silk's Facebook page.<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" /><ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /> On April 26, 2018, at [[Steve King|Rep. Steve King]]'s invitation they testified in front of Congress about their perceived censorship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://steveking.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/diamond-and-silk-uncensored-duo-accepts-steve-king-s-invitation-to|title=Diamond and Silk UNCENSORED: Duo Accepts Steve King's Invitation to Testify|last=|first=|date=April 23, 2018|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"cbsnews congress\" />  Subsequently, Republican members of Congress brought up the two women's censorship claims at [[Mark Zuckerberg]]'s testimony before U.S. Congress.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2018/07/17/republicans-accused-facebook-google-twitter-bias-democrats-called-hearing-dumb/?noredirect=on|title=Republicans accused Facebook, Google and Twitter of bias. Democrats called the hearing 'dumb.'|last=Romm|first=Tony|date=July 17, 2018|work=The Washington Post|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nSince 2018, Diamond and Silk have traveled the country on their ''Chit Chat Tour''.<ref name=\"ChitChatNewsObserver\">{{cite web |url= https://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/politics-columns-blogs/under-the-dome/article208450464.html |title=These black Trump-supporting sisters say Facebook considers them 'unsafe' |first=Brian |last=Murphy |date= April 10, 2018 |work= [[The News & Observer]] |accessdate= August 25, 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"NOLA\"/>\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Louie Gohmert with Diamond And Silk.jpg|thumb|right|Diamond and Silk with [[Louie Gohmert]]]]\nFormerly lifelong [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrats]],<ref name=\"StuartRollingStone\" /> they became [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]] in September 2015, soon after they saw Donald Trump announce his candidacy on television.  According to Hardaway, \"When he announced and we heard everything that he stood for, it was on and poppin\u2019, and we\u2019ve been on the Trump train ever since.\"<ref name=\"AtlanticMonthly\" /> They came to wider prominence in 2015 as Trump supporters after posting a video criticizing former [[Fox News]] host [[Megyn Kelly]] for asking what they considered irrelevant questions during the [[Republican Party presidential debates and forums, 2016|first Republican presidential debate]].<ref name=\"youtube fox business\" />\n\nAlthough officially unaffiliated with the [[Donald Trump presidential campaign, 2016|Trump campaign]], they urged support for Trump via social media efforts and rallies and traveled to three states for the campaign.<ref name=\"Newsweek\" /><ref name=\"nyt\" /> The two women first joined Donald Trump as the \"[[Stump speech (politics)|Stump]] for Trump Girls\" on stage at his [[Raleigh, North Carolina]], rally on December 4, 2015.<ref name=\"guardian 2015-12\" /> They later warmed up the crowd at the Trump rally on January 2, 2016, in [[Biloxi, Mississippi]].<ref name=\"americanmirror 2016-01\" />  They initiated a \"Ditch and Switch\" campaign to encourage Democrats to register as Republicans<ref name=\"StuartRollingStone\"/> and created a website explaining to voters which states had [[Primary elections in the United States#Types of primaries|closed primaries]] and when the deadlines were for changing party affiliations.<ref name=\"nyt\" />\n\nOn November 2, 2016, Diamond and Silk appeared with [[Lara Trump]], wife of [[Eric Trump]], in [[Winston-Salem, North Carolina]], on behalf of the Trump campaign.<ref name=\"journalnow 2016-11\" /> They were paid $1,274.94 for field consulting work by the Trump campaign.<ref name=\"FEC Trump Disbursements\" />\n\nThey regularly appear on Fox News shows including ''[[Hannity]]'', ''[[Fox News Sunday]]'', ''[[Watters' World]]'', and ''[[The Ingraham Angle]]'', and ''[[Fox & Friends]].''<ref name=\"NOLA\" /> In November 2018, Diamond and Silk were given a show on [[Fox Nation]], the online Fox News streaming service.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/418306-trump-supporters-diamond-silk-awarded-program-on-new-fox-news-streaming|title=Trump supporters Diamond & Silk awarded program on new Fox News streaming service|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=2018-11-26|work=TheHill|access-date=2018-11-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thewrap.com/diamond-silk-land-weekly-fox-nation-series/|title=Diamond & Silk Get Their Own Weekly Fox Nation Series|date=2018-11-26|work=TheWrap|access-date=2018-11-26|language=en-US}}</ref> They were covered on ABC's ''[[Nightline]]''.<ref name=\"ABC Nightline\" />  Hardaway is notably more talkative, while Richardson often just expresses agreement.<ref name=\"kansascity\" />\n\nA documentary film by Hardaway and Richardson titled ''[[Dummycrats]]'' premiered in October 2018 at the [[Old Post Office (Washington, D.C.)#Trump International Hotel Washington, D.C.|Trump International Hotel Washington, D.C.]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theepochtimes.com/social-media-stars-diamond-and-silk-go-to-big-screen-for-the-midterms_2691716.html |newspaper=[[The Epoch Times]] |quote=The film premiered at the Trump International Hotel in Washington on Oct. 15 and screened in nearly 800 theaters across the country for a one-night event. |date=October 18, 2018 |title=Social Media Stars Diamond and Silk Go to Big Screen for the Midterms}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Trump Super-Fans Diamond and Silk Announce Michael Moore-Style 'Dummycrats' Movie |url=https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/the-wrap/article/Trump-Super-Fans-Diamond-and-Silk-Announce-13023576.php |website=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |accessdate=July 20, 2018 |date=June 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, during a ''Fox & Friends'' appearance, Diamond and Silk falsely claimed that House Speaker Nancy Pelosi was a \"non-functioning alcoholic\" who \"slurs her words.\" This was in reference to a doctored and slowed down video that appeared to show her slurring her words. Shortly thereafter, ''Fox & Friends'' had to clarify for its viewers that the video was manipulated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/fox-and-friends-admit-diamond-and-silk-mocked-doctored-video-of-crazy-nancy-pelosi|title='Fox & Friends' Admit Diamond & Silk Mocked Doctored Video of 'Crazy Nancy'|last=Messer|first=Olivia|date=2019-05-24|access-date=2019-05-25|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Diamond and Silk appeared in a Trump 2020 re-election advertisement where they gave a pitch for his re-election. At the same time, Diamond and Silk had a weekly show on Fox News' streaming service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/diamond-silk-host-fox-news-streaming-show-being-volunteers-trump-2020-campaign-1215279|title=Diamond and Silk Host Fox News Streaming Show While Being \"Volunteers\" for Trump 2020 Campaign|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-06-08}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020 in the midst of the global [[COVID-19]] pandemic, Hardaway and Richardson claimed that the number of deaths from the pandemic was being inflated in order to make [[Donald Trump]] look incompetent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphopwired.com/playlist/diamond-and-silk-coronavirus-claims/|title=Coontastic Aunties Diamond & Silk Says Coronavirus Numbers Inflated To Make Trump Look Bad|website=HipHopWired|language=en|access-date=2019-06-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/diamond-and-silk-coronavirus-deaths-media-wanting-trump-to-look-bad/|title=Diamond and Silk Attribute Rise in Coronavirus Deaths to Media Wanting to Make Trump Look Bad (Video)|last=Ellefson|first=Lindsey|date=2020-03-31|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n[[File:Diamond and Silk.jpg|thumb|Diamond and Silk [https://twitter.com/DiamondandSilk/status/977569838284656640?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E977569838284656640&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F04%2F14%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fdiamond-silk-facebook.html Official White House Photo]]]\n\n== Politics ==\n===Racial views===\nFollowing the controversial [[Unite the Right rally]] held in [[Charlottesville, Virginia]], on August 11 and 12, 2017, Hardaway and Richardson, appearing on ''[[Fox & Friends]]'', were critical of protesters on both sides in the event.  Hardaway criticized [[Neo-Nazi]] groups and the [[Ku Klux Klan]] for \"spewing hate and&nbsp;... creating violence\" declaring \"all of them should be condemned and denounced. Period\".  In the same interview, she also said she does not \"...&nbsp; like [[Black Lives Matter]] and [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]].\"  They further noted that they feel statues of [[American Civil War|Civil War]] [[Confederate States Army|Confederate soldiers]] should be kept in museums.<ref name=\"FoxNewsInsider\" />\n\nHardaway and Richardson, in December 2017, expressed support for [[Omarosa Manigault Newman]] following her controversial firing as [[White House]] liaison and assistant, faulting the treatment of her by African Americans and the media generally:  \"What I find appalling, to my brothers and sisters [is] how you&nbsp;... can laugh at, pick at, gloat at somebody because they either left the White House or you listened to a salacious story that Miss Piggy went around, running around telling everybody.\" In the same live-stream, they criticized ''[[Good Morning America]]'' anchor [[Robin Roberts (newscaster)|Robin Roberts]] for saying, \"Bye, Felicia\" to Newman during a segment on the ABC show which aired on December 14, 2017.<ref name=\"BlackStar2\" /><ref name=\"ByeFelicia\" />  Addressing Roberts' remarks, Hardaway said, \"How is it that you want the community to come up and then when a sister is sitting at the table, 'Well, she didn\u2019t represent us'? Are you crazy?\"<ref name=\"BlackStar2\"/>\n\n=== 2018 Congressional testimony ===\nOn April 26, 2018, they appeared at a [[United States House Committee on the Judiciary|House Judiciary Committee]] hearing on alleged filtering practices of social media platforms. Representative [[Sheila Jackson Lee]] asked the two women if they had ever received money from the Trump campaign, to which Hardaway responded, \"We have never been paid by the Trump campaign.\" Representative [[Hakeem Jeffries]] suggested that they could be committing perjury and showed them a Federal Election Commission filing which reported that the Trump campaign paid them $1,275 on November 22, 2016 for \"field consulting\".<ref name=SlateJeffries /><ref name=\"thehill congress\" /><ref name=\"cbsnews congress\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk then stated that the payment was reimbursement for the cost of airplane tickets. Following their testimony, ''[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]'' reported that, according to Trump campaign treasurer Bradley Crate, the payment had been categorized incorrectly.  Crate stated, \"The Campaign\u2019s payment to Diamond and Silk for field consulting was based on an invoice they submitted reflecting their costs for air travel to a Campaign event. The invoice was not supported by accompanying receipts, so as a technical matter, could not be reported as a reimbursement even though its purpose was to make them whole for their out-of-pocket costs.\" In the same ''Huffington Post'' article, it was reported that following a $7,025 payment from the campaign of [[Paul Ryan]] primary election challenger [[Paul Nehlen]], Hardaway and Richardson made a campaign video and endorsed Nehlen.<ref name=\"huffpo congress\" />\n\n=== Diamond and Silk Act of 2019 ===\nIn June 2019, House Representative [[Steve King]] joined with Diamond and Silk to introduce the Diamond and Silk Act, an anti\u2013[[sanctuary city]] bill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/house/448489-steve-king-unveils-diamond-and-silk-act-named-for-conservative-youtubers|title=Steve King unveils 'Diamond and Silk Act' named for conservative YouTubers|last=Frazin|first=Rachel|date=2019-06-13|website=TheHill|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/steve-king-introduces-diamond-and-silk-act-press-conference-2019-6|title=Disgraced Rep. Steve King introduces the 'Diamond and Silk Act' in a bizarre press conference that turned into a shouting match|last=Perticone|first=Joe|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-06-16|date=June 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://nymag.com/intelligencer/2019/06/steve-king-diamond-and-silk.html|title=Steve King, Diamond, and Silk Deflect Racism Charges by Unveiling Racist Bill|last=Cheney-Rice|first=Zak|date=2019-06-13|website=Intelligencer|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref> When Diamond and Silk were asked what they thought of King retweeting white supremacists, Hardaway responded, \"I\u2019m tired of you all playing the race card.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> The bill failed to pass the House vote and garnered backlash from both left and right wing media.\n\nThe conservative news magazine [[Washington Examiner]] criticized King for mocking homelessness and veteran's issues with the bill,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollcall.com/2019/06/11/rep-kings-diamond-and-silk-act-gets-ripped-by-conservative-pundits/ |title=Rep. King\u2019s 'Diamond and Silk Act' gets ripped by conservative pundits |first=Griffin |last=Connolly |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Roll Call |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> and described the Diamond and Silk Act of 2019 as being \"named for a clownish YouTube duo who have leveraged their online popularity into regular appearances on Fox News\". <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/opinion/rep-steve-king-makes-a-mockery-of-homelessness-veterans-issues |title=Rep. Steve King makes a mockery of homelessness, veterans issues |first=Becket |last=Adams |date=June 10, 2019 |website=Washington Examiner |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Platforms ==\n=== YouTube ===\nHardaway and Richardson have asserted that [[YouTube]] has discriminated against them through [[Censorship by Google#Advertiser-friendly content|demonetization]] of their channel because of their support for Trump.<ref name=\"FoxNewsInsider\"/><ref name=\"Outline\" />\n\n=== Facebook ===\nIn an April 2018 [[Twitter|tweet]] and [[Facebook]] post, Hardaway and Richardson reproduced a message from Facebook stating that the Diamond and Silk Facebook page's content and brand were deemed to be \"unsafe to the community.\" According to Hardaway and Richardson, the message sent from the Facebook policy team concluded with: \"This decision is final and it is not appeal-able in any way.\"  The pair stated that they believed that they had been victims of censorship by Facebook after receiving a communication from the social media website's policy team. \n\nBoth women stated they had started questioning Facebook via phone calls, emails, and chat sessions as to their alleged \"bias censorship and discrimination against D&S brand page\" in September 2017.  Both women have stated a reduction in reactions to their posts and videos since that time period, and that followers no longer receive notifications about posts and videos.  As of April 2018, their Facebook page states they have nearly 1.3 million followers.<ref name=\"Facebookpage\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk's censorship claims were uncritically repeated in right-wing media.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> According to CNN, their claims likely influenced an April 2018 congressional hearing which involved Mark Zuckerberg after the [[Cambridge Analytica]] scandal.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> ''Business Insider'' noted that Diamond and Silk were a \"frequent topic\" during that hearing.<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /> [[Tennessee]] Republican [[Marsha Blackburn|Representative Marsha Blackburn]] finished her questioning of Zuckerberg by stating, \"Let me tell you something right now, Diamond and Silk is not terrorism\". [[Texas]] Republican [[Joe Barton|Representative Joe Barton]] asked Zuckerberg, \"Why is Facebook censoring conservative bloggers such as Diamond and Silk?\"  Zuckerberg responded that Facebook employees had made an error and they had contacted Hardaway and Richardson.<ref name=\"CNET\" /><ref name=\"Newsweek3\" />\n\nWhile there is no evidence that Diamond and Silk were censored or that their page was blocked by Facebook, the pair continues to contend it was.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /><ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" /><ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /> Facebook's own analytics firm showed that the Diamond and Silk page had not lost a significant amount of influence on the social network.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> By the time that Diamond and Silk spoke at a congressional hearing about their censorship claims, news outlets such as [[CNN]] and [[Business Insider]] described their censorship claims as debunked.<ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /><ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /> At the hearing, experts testified that there was no evidence that Diamond and Silk had been targeted.<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /> According to ''[[The Washington Post]]'', \"the numbers do not bear out the argument that the sisters have been repressed.\"<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk stated that Facebook had not contacted them. Facebook said they attempted contact via email, Twitter, phone, and Facebook Messenger.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /><ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" />  The pair later said that messages sent to them through email should not be expected to be read, because they receive many emails.<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" />\n\n== Response ==\nArtist and activist [[Bree Newsome]] has described Hardaway and Richardson as \"a modern-day [[minstrel show]]\" and stated in an interview that the pair's presentation relies on \"stereotypical images of black women\".<ref name=\"nyt newsome boykin\"/> [[Keith Boykin]] argued that, \"the way they speak, the way they talk and act and behave [... if they] were saying anything that was contradictory to Trump, the Trump supporters who defend them would be the first to attack them.\" Boykin argued that conservatives give attention to Hardaway and Richardson because they \"only want to listen to the people who reaffirm their narrow, limited vision of what blackness is all about and how black people should perceive white people and specifically how they should perceive Donald Trump.\"<ref name=\"nyt newsome boykin\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/14/us/politics/diamond-silk-facebook.html |title=Who Are Diamond and Silk? A Look at 2 Pro-Trump Social Media Stars |last=Stack |first=Liam |date=April 14, 2018 |website=The New York Times |access-date=August 5, 2018|url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist|refs =\n<ref name=\"huffpo congress\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/diamond-and-silk-appear-lie-under-oath-about-trump-payments_us_5ae2111ae4b055fd7fc9a78b |title=Diamond And Silk Appear To Lie Under Oath About Trump Payments |last=Nelson |first=Eliot  |date=April 26, 2018 |website=huffingtonpost.com |access-date=April 26, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=SlateJeffries>[https://slate.com/technology/2018/04/did-diamond-and-silk-actually-lie-under-oath.html Did Diamond and Silk Actually Lie Under Oath?]. [[Slate (magazine)|Slate]], April 26, 2018</ref>\n<ref name=\"thehill congress\">{{Cite news|url=http://thehill.com/policy/technology/385013-diamond-and-silk-say-under-oath-they-werent-paid-by-trump-campaign-fec|title=Diamond and Silk say under oath they weren't paid by Trump campaign; FEC filings say otherwise|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=April 26, 2018|work=TheHill|access-date=May 2, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"cbsnews congress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/pro-trump-social-media-personalities-diamond-and-silk-testify-before-congress-live-stream/|title=Pro-Trump social media stars Diamond and Silk testify under oath|access-date=April 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\">{{Cite news|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/diamond-and-silk-facebook-censorship-testimony-2018-4?r=US&IR=T|title=Trump vloggers Diamond & Silk are sticking to their debunked claim about Facebook censorship|last=|first=|date=|work=Business Insider|access-date=April 28, 2018|language=en|quote=Hardaway and Richardson said, as they have many times in appearances on Fox News, that they were not contacted by Facebook in any official capacity... But messages obtained by conservative commentator Erick Erickson show that Facebook reached out to Hardaway and Richardson several times through phone, Facebook Messenger, and multiple email addresses.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Outline\">{{cite web |url=https://theoutline.com/post/2258/youtube-is-leaving-its-creators-in-the-dark?zd=1&zi=odwzc43b |title=YouTube is leaving its creators in the dark |last=Birnbaum |first=Ian |date=September 18, 2017 |website=The Outline |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ABC Nightline\">{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/proud-donald-trump-supporting-sister-act-diamond-silk/story?id=38166582 |title=A Look at Proud Donald Trump-Supporting Sister Act 'Diamond and Silk' |last=Marjorie McAfee, Ashley Louszko |first=Byron Pitts |date=April 5, 2016 |access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n<!-- not used in article\n<ref name=\"Newsweek2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.newsweek.com/2016/07/22/donald-trumps-loud-proud-and-pissed-female-supporters-480153.html |title=DONALD TRUMP'S LOUD, PROUD AND PISSED OFF FEMALE SUPPORTERS |last=Gorman |first=Michelle |date=July 14, 2016 |website=Newsweek.com |access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"StuartRollingStone\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/features/meet-the-black-women-defending-trumps-record-on-race-w441709 |title= Meet the Black Women Defending Trump's Record on Race |first=Tessa |last=Stuart |date= September 28, 2016 |work= [[Rolling Stone]] |quote= Like Trump himself, Diamond and Silk are new to the Republican party. Lifelong Democrats, they switched parties so they could cast their votes for him in the North Carolina primary.|accessdate= January 28, 2018 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"youtube fox business\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-piJWc_6Lqc Former Democrats Stump For Trump.  Fox Business, Varney and Co.] January 8, 2016</ref>\n<ref name=\"AtlanticMonthly\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/01/donald-trump-democrats/433503/ |title=Meet the YouTube Stars Trying to Convert Democrats to Team Trump |last=Foran |first=Clare  |date=January 29, 2016 |website=The Atlantic |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Newsweek\">{{cite web |url=http://www.newsweek.com/pro-trump-youtubers-diamond-silk-build-their-brand-hand-trump-administration-649318 |title=Pro-Trump Youtubers Diamond and Silk 'Build Their Brand' with a hand from the Trump Administration |last=Lanktree |first=Graham |date=August 10, 2017 |website=Newsweek |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"nyt\">[https://www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2016/01/06/supporters-seek-to-persuade-democrats-to-ditch-and-switch-for-donald-trump/ Supporters Seek to Persuade Democrats to \u2018Ditch and Switch\u2019 for Donald Trump], New York Times, January 7, 2016.</ref>\n<ref name=\"guardian 2015-12\">[http://guardianlv.com/2015/12/donald-trump-supporters-diamond-and-silk-a-comedy-act/ Donald Trump Supporters Diamond and Silk a Comedy Act?], Liberty Voice, December 9, 2015.</ref>\n<ref name=\"americanmirror 2016-01\">[http://www.theamericanmirror.com/video-stump-for-trump-duo-rock-capacity-crowd-at-ms-rally/ \u2018Stump for Trump\u2019 duo rock capacity crowd at MS rally], The American Mirror, January 3, 2016.</ref>\n<ref name=\"journalnow 2016-11\">{{cite news |date=November 2, 2016 |title=Diamond and Silk, Lara Trump bring Women for Trump tour to Winston-Salem |url=http://www.journalnow.com/news/local/diamond-and-silk-lara-trump-bring-women-for-trump-tour/article_9991442a-a10f-11e6-a433-63ff4b48083e.html |newspaper=[[Winston-Salem Journal]] |location=[[Winston-Salem, North Carolina]] |access-date=November 18, 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"FEC Trump Disbursements\">{{cite web |url=http://docquery.fec.gov/cgi-bin/forms/C00580100/1133930/sb/ALL/4 |title=FEC Donald J. Trump for President, Inc. Itemized Disbursements |access-date=April 30, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NOLA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nola.com/tv/index.ssf/2018/03/fox_news_darlings_diamond_and.html |title=Fox News darlings Diamond and Silk bringing 'Chit Chat Tour' to New Orleans |last=Morris |first=Melinda  |date=March 20, 2018 |website=NOLA.com The Times Picayune |access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"kansascity\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kansascity.com/news/nation-world/article208473664.html|title=Mark Zuckerberg: Facebook made 'enforcement error' with Trump fans Diamond and Silk|last=Gutierrez|first=Lisa|date=April 10, 2018|work=The Kansas City Star}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"FoxNewsInsider\">{{cite web |url=http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/08/13/diamond-silk-dont-white-nationalists-antifa |title=Diamond and Silk: We Don't Like White Nationalists or Antifa |date=August 13, 2017 |website=Fox News Insider |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"BlackStar2\">{{cite web |url=http://atlantablackstar.com/2017/12/29/omarosa-gets-defended-diamond-silk-trump-supporters-get-dragged/ |title=Omarosa Gets Defended by Diamond and Silk \u2026 and the Trump Supporters Get Dragged - You may not like Omarosa, but you don't have a right to laugh at her |last=Willis |first=Kiersten  |date=December 29, 2017 |website=Atlanta Black Star |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ByeFelicia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/12/14/gma-host-robin-roberts-omarosas-white-house-exit-bye-felicia/951679001/ |title='GMA' host Robin Roberts on Omarosa's White House exit: 'Bye, Felicia' |last=Deerwester |first=Jayme |date=December 14, 2017 |website=USA Today |access-date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Facebookpage\">{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.facebook.com/DiamondandSilk/?ref=br_rs |title=Diamond and Silk@DiamondandSilk |date=April 8, 2018 |last=Silk |first=Diamond and |type=Social media}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"cnn facebook\">{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2018/04/15/media/diamond-silk-facebook-fox-news/index.html|title=Led by Fox News, pro-Trump media fuels false narrative to accuse Facebook of censorship|last=Darcy|first=Oliver|date=|work=CNNMoney |access-date=April 26, 2018|quote=the Diamond & Silk page was never banned. It was never taken down. It was never censored... The tidal wave of media coverage didn't just mislead viewers; it likely influenced the Mark Zuckerberg hearings on Capitol Hill. Several lawmakers chose to use at least a portion of their time questioning the Facebook chief to ask him about the supposed censorship of Hardaway and Richardson. The hearings were scheduled to address Facebook's use and protection of user data in the wake of the Cambridge Analytica scandal.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"CNET\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/who-are-diamond-silk-and-what-do-they-have-to-do-with-facebooks-mark-zuckerberg/|title=Who are Diamond and Silk, and what do they have to do with Facebook?|last=Ng|first=Alfred|date=April 11, 2018|website=CNET.com|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Newsweek3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsweek.com/diamond-and-silk-facebook-zuckerberg-882332|title=Diamond and Silk hit back at Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook 'censorship': 'We are not terrorists' |last=Kutner|first=Max|date=April 11, 2018|access-date=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\">{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2018/04/26/media/diamond-and-silk-hearing/index.html|title=The Diamond and Silk show goes to Washington|last=Darcy|first=Oliver|date=|work=CNNMoney|access-date=April 28, 2018|quote=They had not been censored. Hardaway and Richardson's claims had been thoroughly debunked.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"thehill cuomo\">{{Cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/media/385176-chris-cuomo-confronts-gop-lawmaker-over-diamond-silks-claims-of-censorship|title=Chris Cuomo confronts GOP lawmaker over Diamond and Silk's claims of censorship|last=Bowden|first=John|date=April 27, 2018|work=TheHill|access-date=April 28, 2018|language=en|quote=The two pro-Trump personalities allege that a number of social media platforms, including Facebook, censored their content using algorithms to prevent it from showing up on users' feeds. They have provided no evidence for they claim, which Facebook and other companies deny. In addition, the two were found to have erroneously claimed that Facebook did not contact them over their concerns, despite an investigation showing that Facebook reps attempted to reach out to the two over email.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/diamond-and-silk-how-two-small-town-north-carolina-sisters-found-fame-as-trump-fans/2018/04/26/1de3f50a-4723-11e8-9072-f6d4bc32f223_story.html|title=Who are Diamond and Silk? How two small-town ex-Democrats found fame as 'warriors' for Trump.|last=Hesse|first=Monica|date=April 26, 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=April 28, 2018|last2=Zak|first2=Dan|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286|quote=Experts testified in Congress that there\u2019s no evidence of targeting... The numbers do not bear out the argument that the sisters have been repressed.}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.diamondandsilkinc.com}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCug1cL7vmUvYooOjXyHjsxQ/videos YouTube channel \"The Viewers View\"]\n* [https://twitter.com/DiamondandSilk Official Twitter account]\n* [http://www.facebook.com/DiamondandSilk/?ref=br_rs Official Facebook page]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diamond and Silk}}\n[[Category:21st-century African-American activists]]\n[[Category:Activists from North Carolina]]\n[[Category:African-American bloggers]]\n[[Category:American bloggers]]\n[[Category:African-American Christians]]\n[[Category:African-American people in North Carolina politics]]\n[[Category:African-American women in politics]]\n[[Category:American media personalities]]\n[[Category:American political activists]]\n[[Category:American political blogs]]\n[[Category:American women bloggers]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Donald Trump 2016 presidential campaign]]\n[[Category:Entertainer duos]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:North Carolina Republicans]]\n[[Category:People associated with the 2016 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:Video bloggers]]\n[[Category:Women in North Carolina politics]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American video bloggers}}\n \n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Diamond and Silk\n| image              = File:Diamond and Silk on Info Wars April 2018.jpg\n| image_size         = 240px\n| caption            = Diamond and Silk (left to right) on ''[[InfoWars]]'' in 2018\n| birth_name         = Lynnette Hardaway (\"Diamond\")<br /> Rochelle Richardson (\"Silk\")\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| residence          = [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]]\n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| education          = \n| occupation         = Social media personalities, political activists\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = The Viewers View\n| home_town          = [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]], U.S. \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- {{height|cm=X}} OR {{height|ft=X|in=Y}}-->\n| weight             = <!-- {{convert|X|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} or {{convert|X|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}} -->\n| television         = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| ethnicity          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] (2015\u2013present) <br /> [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] (until 2015)\n}}\n\t\n'''Lynnette Hardaway''' and '''Rochelle Richardson''', known as '''Diamond and Silk''', are American live-stream video bloggers, social media personalities, political activists and [[Fox Nation]] hosts.  They are known for their commentary in support of United States President [[Donald Trump]].\n\nThe two women received media attention during the 2016 campaign and again in April 2018 when they alleged that [[Facebook]] had notified them they were \"unsafe to the community.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://judiciary.house.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Diamond-and-Silk-Testimony.pdf|title=Diamond and Silk Testimony to House Judiciary Committee|website=Judiciary Committee, US House of Representatives|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121210526/https://judiciary.house.gov/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Diamond-and-Silk-Testimony.pdf|archive-date=November 21, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>  In response, they accused Facebook of blocking and censoring their Facebook page.  There is, however, no evidence that Facebook blocked or censored Diamond and Silk's Facebook page.<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" /><ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /> On April 26, 2018, at [[Steve King|Rep. Steve King]]'s invitation they testified in front of Congress about their perceived censorship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://steveking.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/diamond-and-silk-uncensored-duo-accepts-steve-king-s-invitation-to|title=Diamond and Silk UNCENSORED: Duo Accepts Steve King's Invitation to Testify|last=|first=|date=April 23, 2018|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"cbsnews congress\" />  Subsequently, Republican members of Congress brought up the two women's censorship claims at [[Mark Zuckerberg]]'s testimony before U.S. Congress.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2018/07/17/republicans-accused-facebook-google-twitter-bias-democrats-called-hearing-dumb/?noredirect=on|title=Republicans accused Facebook, Google and Twitter of bias. Democrats called the hearing 'dumb.'|last=Romm|first=Tony|date=July 17, 2018|work=The Washington Post|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nSince 2018, Diamond and Silk have traveled the country on their ''Chit Chat Tour''.<ref name=\"ChitChatNewsObserver\">{{cite web |url= https://www.newsobserver.com/news/politics-government/politics-columns-blogs/under-the-dome/article208450464.html |title=These black Trump-supporting sisters say Facebook considers them 'unsafe' |first=Brian |last=Murphy |date= April 10, 2018 |work= [[The News & Observer]] |accessdate= August 25, 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"NOLA\"/>\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Louie Gohmert with Diamond And Silk.jpg|thumb|right|Diamond and Silk with [[Louie Gohmert]]]]\nFormerly lifelong [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrats]],<ref name=\"StuartRollingStone\" /> they became [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]] in September 2015, soon after they saw Donald Trump announce his candidacy on television.  According to Hardaway, \"When he announced and we heard everything that he stood for, it was on and poppin\u2019, and we\u2019ve been on the Trump train ever since.\"<ref name=\"AtlanticMonthly\" /> They came to wider prominence in 2015 as Trump supporters after posting a video criticizing former [[Fox News]] host [[Megyn Kelly]] for asking what they considered irrelevant questions during the [[Republican Party presidential debates and forums, 2016|first Republican presidential debate]].<ref name=\"youtube fox business\" />\n\nAlthough officially unaffiliated with the [[Donald Trump presidential campaign, 2016|Trump campaign]], they urged support for Trump via social media efforts and rallies and traveled to three states for the campaign.<ref name=\"Newsweek\" /><ref name=\"nyt\" /> The two women first joined Donald Trump as the \"[[Stump speech (politics)|Stump]] for Trump Girls\" on stage at his [[Raleigh, North Carolina]], rally on December 4, 2015.<ref name=\"guardian 2015-12\" /> They later warmed up the crowd at the Trump rally on January 2, 2016, in [[Biloxi, Mississippi]].<ref name=\"americanmirror 2016-01\" />  They initiated a \"Ditch and Switch\" campaign to encourage Democrats to register as Republicans<ref name=\"StuartRollingStone\"/> and created a website explaining to voters which states had [[Primary elections in the United States#Types of primaries|closed primaries]] and when the deadlines were for changing party affiliations.<ref name=\"nyt\" />\n\nOn November 2, 2016, Diamond and Silk appeared with [[Lara Trump]], wife of [[Eric Trump]], in [[Winston-Salem, North Carolina]], on behalf of the Trump campaign.<ref name=\"journalnow 2016-11\" /> They were paid $1,274.94 for field consulting work by the Trump campaign.<ref name=\"FEC Trump Disbursements\" />\n\nThey regularly appear on Fox News shows including ''[[Hannity]]'', ''[[Fox News Sunday]]'', ''[[Watters' World]]'', and ''[[The Ingraham Angle]]'', and ''[[Fox & Friends]].''<ref name=\"NOLA\" /> In November 2018, Diamond and Silk were given a show on [[Fox Nation]], the online Fox News streaming service.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/418306-trump-supporters-diamond-silk-awarded-program-on-new-fox-news-streaming|title=Trump supporters Diamond & Silk awarded program on new Fox News streaming service|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=2018-11-26|work=TheHill|access-date=2018-11-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thewrap.com/diamond-silk-land-weekly-fox-nation-series/|title=Diamond & Silk Get Their Own Weekly Fox Nation Series|date=2018-11-26|work=TheWrap|access-date=2018-11-26|language=en-US}}</ref> They were covered on ABC's ''[[Nightline]]''.<ref name=\"ABC Nightline\" />  Hardaway is notably more talkative, while Richardson often just expresses agreement.<ref name=\"kansascity\" />\n\nA documentary film by Hardaway and Richardson titled ''[[Dummycrats]]'' premiered in October 2018 at the [[Old Post Office (Washington, D.C.)#Trump International Hotel Washington, D.C.|Trump International Hotel Washington, D.C.]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theepochtimes.com/social-media-stars-diamond-and-silk-go-to-big-screen-for-the-midterms_2691716.html |newspaper=[[The Epoch Times]] |quote=The film premiered at the Trump International Hotel in Washington on Oct. 15 and screened in nearly 800 theaters across the country for a one-night event. |date=October 18, 2018 |title=Social Media Stars Diamond and Silk Go to Big Screen for the Midterms}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Trump Super-Fans Diamond and Silk Announce Michael Moore-Style 'Dummycrats' Movie |url=https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/the-wrap/article/Trump-Super-Fans-Diamond-and-Silk-Announce-13023576.php |website=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |accessdate=July 20, 2018 |date=June 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, during a ''Fox & Friends'' appearance, Diamond and Silk falsely claimed that House Speaker Nancy Pelosi was a \"non-functioning alcoholic\" who \"slurs her words.\" This was in reference to a doctored and slowed down video that appeared to show her slurring her words. Shortly thereafter, ''Fox & Friends'' had to clarify for its viewers that the video was manipulated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/fox-and-friends-admit-diamond-and-silk-mocked-doctored-video-of-crazy-nancy-pelosi|title='Fox & Friends' Admit Diamond & Silk Mocked Doctored Video of 'Crazy Nancy'|last=Messer|first=Olivia|date=2019-05-24|access-date=2019-05-25|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Diamond and Silk appeared in a Trump 2020 re-election advertisement where they gave a pitch for his re-election. At the same time, Diamond and Silk had a weekly show on Fox News' streaming service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/diamond-silk-host-fox-news-streaming-show-being-volunteers-trump-2020-campaign-1215279|title=Diamond and Silk Host Fox News Streaming Show While Being \"Volunteers\" for Trump 2020 Campaign|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-06-08}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020 in the midst of the global [[COVID-19]] pandemic, Hardaway and Richardson claimed that the number of deaths from the pandemic was being inflated in order to make [[Donald Trump]] look incompetent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hiphopwired.com/playlist/diamond-and-silk-coronavirus-claims/|title=Coontastic Aunties Diamond & Silk Says Coronavirus Numbers Inflated To Make Trump Look Bad|website=HipHopWired|language=en|access-date=2019-06-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/diamond-and-silk-coronavirus-deaths-media-wanting-trump-to-look-bad/|title=Diamond and Silk Attribute Rise in Coronavirus Deaths to Media Wanting to Make Trump Look Bad (Video)|last=Ellefson|first=Lindsey|date=2020-03-31|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n[[File:Diamond and Silk.jpg|thumb|Diamond and Silk [https://twitter.com/DiamondandSilk/status/977569838284656640?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E977569838284656640&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F04%2F14%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fdiamond-silk-facebook.html Official White House Photo]]]\n\n== Politics ==\n===Racial views===\nFollowing the controversial [[Unite the Right rally]] held in [[Charlottesville, Virginia]], on August 11 and 12, 2017, Hardaway and Richardson, appearing on ''[[Fox & Friends]]'', were critical of protesters on both sides in the event.  Hardaway criticized [[Neo-Nazi]] groups and the [[Ku Klux Klan]] for \"spewing hate and&nbsp;... creating violence\" declaring \"all of them should be condemned and denounced. Period\".  In the same interview, she also said she does not \"...&nbsp; like [[Black Lives Matter]] and [[Antifa (United States)|Antifa]].\"  They further noted that they feel statues of [[American Civil War|Civil War]] [[Confederate States Army|Confederate soldiers]] should be kept in museums.<ref name=\"FoxNewsInsider\" />\n\nHardaway and Richardson, in December 2017, expressed support for [[Omarosa Manigault Newman]] following her controversial firing as [[White House]] liaison and assistant, faulting the treatment of her by African Americans and the media generally:  \"What I find appalling, to my brothers and sisters [is] how you&nbsp;... can laugh at, pick at, gloat at somebody because they either left the White House or you listened to a salacious story that Miss Piggy went around, running around telling everybody.\" In the same live-stream, they criticized ''[[Good Morning America]]'' anchor [[Robin Roberts (newscaster)|Robin Roberts]] for saying, \"Bye, Felicia\" to Newman during a segment on the ABC show which aired on December 14, 2017.<ref name=\"BlackStar2\" /><ref name=\"ByeFelicia\" />  Addressing Roberts' remarks, Hardaway said, \"How is it that you want the community to come up and then when a sister is sitting at the table, 'Well, she didn\u2019t represent us'? Are you crazy?\"<ref name=\"BlackStar2\"/>\n\n=== 2018 Congressional testimony ===\nOn April 26, 2018, they appeared at a [[United States House Committee on the Judiciary|House Judiciary Committee]] hearing on alleged filtering practices of social media platforms. Representative [[Sheila Jackson Lee]] asked the two women if they had ever received money from the Trump campaign, to which Hardaway responded, \"We have never been paid by the Trump campaign.\" Representative [[Hakeem Jeffries]] suggested that they could be committing perjury and showed them a Federal Election Commission filing which reported that the Trump campaign paid them $1,275 on November 22, 2016 for \"field consulting\".<ref name=SlateJeffries /><ref name=\"thehill congress\" /><ref name=\"cbsnews congress\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk then stated that the payment was reimbursement for the cost of airplane tickets. Following their testimony, ''[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]'' reported that, according to Trump campaign treasurer Bradley Crate, the payment had been categorized incorrectly.  Crate stated, \"The Campaign\u2019s payment to Diamond and Silk for field consulting was based on an invoice they submitted reflecting their costs for air travel to a Campaign event. The invoice was not supported by accompanying receipts, so as a technical matter, could not be reported as a reimbursement even though its purpose was to make them whole for their out-of-pocket costs.\" In the same ''Huffington Post'' article, it was reported that following a $7,025 payment from the campaign of [[Paul Ryan]] primary election challenger [[Paul Nehlen]], Hardaway and Richardson made a campaign video and endorsed Nehlen.<ref name=\"huffpo congress\" />\n\n=== Diamond and Silk Act of 2019 ===\nIn June 2019, House Representative [[Steve King]] joined with Diamond and Silk to introduce the Diamond and Silk Act, an anti\u2013[[sanctuary city]] bill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/house/448489-steve-king-unveils-diamond-and-silk-act-named-for-conservative-youtubers|title=Steve King unveils 'Diamond and Silk Act' named for conservative YouTubers|last=Frazin|first=Rachel|date=2019-06-13|website=TheHill|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/steve-king-introduces-diamond-and-silk-act-press-conference-2019-6|title=Disgraced Rep. Steve King introduces the 'Diamond and Silk Act' in a bizarre press conference that turned into a shouting match|last=Perticone|first=Joe|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-06-16|date=June 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://nymag.com/intelligencer/2019/06/steve-king-diamond-and-silk.html|title=Steve King, Diamond, and Silk Deflect Racism Charges by Unveiling Racist Bill|last=Cheney-Rice|first=Zak|date=2019-06-13|website=Intelligencer|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref> When Diamond and Silk were asked what they thought of King retweeting white supremacists, Hardaway responded, \"I\u2019m tired of you all playing the race card.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> The bill failed to pass the House vote and garnered backlash from both left and right wing media.\n\nThe conservative news magazine [[Washington Examiner]] criticized King for mocking homelessness and veteran's issues with the bill,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollcall.com/2019/06/11/rep-kings-diamond-and-silk-act-gets-ripped-by-conservative-pundits/ |title=Rep. King\u2019s 'Diamond and Silk Act' gets ripped by conservative pundits |first=Griffin |last=Connolly |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Roll Call |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> and described the Diamond and Silk Act of 2019 as being \"named for a clownish YouTube duo who have leveraged their online popularity into regular appearances on Fox News\". <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/opinion/rep-steve-king-makes-a-mockery-of-homelessness-veterans-issues |title=Rep. Steve King makes a mockery of homelessness, veterans issues |first=Becket |last=Adams |date=June 10, 2019 |website=Washington Examiner |access-date=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Platforms ==\n=== YouTube ===\nHardaway and Richardson have asserted that [[YouTube]] has discriminated against them through [[Censorship by Google#Advertiser-friendly content|demonetization]] of their channel because of their support for Trump.<ref name=\"FoxNewsInsider\"/><ref name=\"Outline\" />\n\n=== Facebook ===\nIn an April 2018 [[Twitter|tweet]] and [[Facebook]] post, Hardaway and Richardson reproduced a message from Facebook stating that the Diamond and Silk Facebook page's content and brand were deemed to be \"unsafe to the community.\" According to Hardaway and Richardson, the message sent from the Facebook policy team concluded with: \"This decision is final and it is not appeal-able in any way.\"  The pair stated that they believed that they had been victims of censorship by Facebook after receiving a communication from the social media website's policy team. \n\nBoth women stated they had started questioning Facebook via phone calls, emails, and chat sessions as to their alleged \"bias censorship and discrimination against D&S brand page\" in September 2017.  Both women have stated a reduction in reactions to their posts and videos since that time period, and that followers no longer receive notifications about posts and videos.  As of April 2018, their Facebook page states they have nearly 1.3 million followers.<ref name=\"Facebookpage\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk's censorship claims were uncritically repeated in right-wing media.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> According to CNN, their claims likely influenced an April 2018 congressional hearing which involved Mark Zuckerberg after the [[Cambridge Analytica]] scandal.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> ''Business Insider'' noted that Diamond and Silk were a \"frequent topic\" during that hearing.<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /> [[Tennessee]] Republican [[Marsha Blackburn|Representative Marsha Blackburn]] finished her questioning of Zuckerberg by stating, \"Let me tell you something right now, Diamond and Silk is not terrorism\". [[Texas]] Republican [[Joe Barton|Representative Joe Barton]] asked Zuckerberg, \"Why is Facebook censoring conservative bloggers such as Diamond and Silk?\"  Zuckerberg responded that Facebook employees had made an error and they had contacted Hardaway and Richardson.<ref name=\"CNET\" /><ref name=\"Newsweek3\" />\n\nWhile there is no evidence that Diamond and Silk were censored or that their page was blocked by Facebook, the pair continues to contend it was.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /><ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" /><ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /> Facebook's own analytics firm showed that the Diamond and Silk page had not lost a significant amount of influence on the social network.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /> By the time that Diamond and Silk spoke at a congressional hearing about their censorship claims, news outlets such as [[CNN]] and [[Business Insider]] described their censorship claims as debunked.<ref name=\"cnn congress hearing\" /><ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /> At the hearing, experts testified that there was no evidence that Diamond and Silk had been targeted.<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" /> According to ''[[The Washington Post]]'', \"the numbers do not bear out the argument that the sisters have been repressed.\"<ref name=\"washingtonpost found fame\" />\n\nDiamond and Silk stated that Facebook had not contacted them. Facebook said they attempted contact via email, Twitter, phone, and Facebook Messenger.<ref name=\"cnn facebook\" /><ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" /><ref name=\"thehill cuomo\" />  The pair later said that messages sent to them through email should not be expected to be read, because they receive many emails.<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\" />\n\n== Response ==\nArtist and activist [[Bree Newsome]] has described Hardaway and Richardson as \"a modern-day [[minstrel show]]\" and stated in an interview that the pair's presentation relies on \"stereotypical images of black women\".<ref name=\"nyt newsome boykin\"/> [[Keith Boykin]] argued that, \"the way they speak, the way they talk and act and behave [... if they] were saying anything that was contradictory to Trump, the Trump supporters who defend them would be the first to attack them.\" Boykin argued that conservatives give attention to Hardaway and Richardson because they \"only want to listen to the people who reaffirm their narrow, limited vision of what blackness is all about and how black people should perceive white people and specifically how they should perceive Donald Trump.\"<ref name=\"nyt newsome boykin\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/14/us/politics/diamond-silk-facebook.html |title=Who Are Diamond and Silk? A Look at 2 Pro-Trump Social Media Stars |last=Stack |first=Liam |date=April 14, 2018 |website=The New York Times |access-date=August 5, 2018|url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist|refs =\n<ref name=\"huffpo congress\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/diamond-and-silk-appear-lie-under-oath-about-trump-payments_us_5ae2111ae4b055fd7fc9a78b |title=Diamond And Silk Appear To Lie Under Oath About Trump Payments |last=Nelson |first=Eliot  |date=April 26, 2018 |website=huffingtonpost.com |access-date=April 26, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=SlateJeffries>[https://slate.com/technology/2018/04/did-diamond-and-silk-actually-lie-under-oath.html Did Diamond and Silk Actually Lie Under Oath?]. [[Slate (magazine)|Slate]], April 26, 2018</ref>\n<ref name=\"thehill congress\">{{Cite news|url=http://thehill.com/policy/technology/385013-diamond-and-silk-say-under-oath-they-werent-paid-by-trump-campaign-fec|title=Diamond and Silk say under oath they weren't paid by Trump campaign; FEC filings say otherwise|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=April 26, 2018|work=TheHill|access-date=May 2, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"cbsnews congress\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/pro-trump-social-media-personalities-diamond-and-silk-testify-before-congress-live-stream/|title=Pro-Trump social media stars Diamond and Silk testify under oath|access-date=April 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"businessinsider congress\">{{Cite news|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/diamond-and-silk-facebook-censorship-testimony-2018-4?r=US&IR=T|title=Trump vloggers Diamond & Silk are sticking to their debunked claim about Facebook censorship|last=|first=|date=|work=Business Insider|access-date=April 28, 2018|language=en|quote=Hardaway and Richardson said, as they have many times in appearances on Fox News, that they were not contacted by Facebook in any official capacity... But messages obtained by conservative commentator Erick Erickson show that Facebook reached out to Hardaway and Richardson several times through phone, Facebook Messenger, and multiple email addresses.}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Outline\">{{cite web |url=https://theoutline.com/post/2258/youtube-is-leaving-its-creators-in-the-dark?zd=1&zi=odwzc43b |title=YouTube 